Kolani Stormynytes<br>
<br>
First thing's first. If you want to raid with another guild that is your choice. It is also there right to require you to do what ever they want on there raid. You can decline and not raid or try and argue your piont or whatever, but the final say as to what has to happen on any given &quot;guild&quot; raid is that of the guild. Now that being said Before I was a member I raided as a guest I was never even asked to go anon. I have seen many many many people attend raids with us as guests and none that I know of has ever been told that they needed to deguild to attend. We do have a rule that guest are alowed on only 3 raids before they must either app to us or they will no long be able to raid with us, however there are many exceptions to that rule. (And I can site examples if I must, but like I said I have never heard of anything remotley like what you said happinging.) <br>
<br>
